remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoderFrame` represents a single frame in an animated WebP image. Each frame combines pixel data (as an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPixmap>) with a display duration. Construct frames from bitmaps, images, or pixmaps and pass them to <xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated(SkiaSharp.SKWStream,System.ReadOnlySpan{SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame},SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderOptions)>.

The pixel data source provided at construction time is converted to an `SKPixmap` internally. The frame does not own or dispose the source object.

## Examples

```csharp
var frames = new SKWebpEncoderFrame[]
{
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bitmap1, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100)),
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bitmap2, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100)),
};

var options = SKWebpEncoderOptions.Default;
using var data = SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated(frames, options);
if (data is not null)
    File.WriteAllBytes("animation.webp", data.ToArray());
```
